\subsection{$\AffineCoverMVSquare.X_4$ specialisation (iter-035)}

With the iter-034 universal bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$ in scope, the natural specialisation lands the bridge on the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$. Iter-029's simp lemma $\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare\_toSquare\_X_4} : S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4 = \top$ identifies the corner with the top open of the underlying scheme; Mathlib's $\mathtt{Preorder.isTerminalTop}$ supplies a witness $\IsTerminal\,(\top : \mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})$. Composing the equation (transported via $\mathtt{Eq.symm} \blacktriangleright$) with the universal bridge gives the desired specialisation. The qualified $\mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}$ form is required to sidestep the iter-029 sub-namespace shadowing trap.

\begin{definition}[$\AffineCoverMVSquare.X_4$ specialisation, abstract sheaf form, iter-035]
  \label{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_X₄_linearEquiv}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_eq_HModule_linearEquiv, def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare, def:Scheme_HModule, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  Let $k$ be a field, $X : \Scheme$, $S : X.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $F : \Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, $n : \N$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for the same sheaf category. There is a $k$-linear isomorphism
  \[
    \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)
    \;\equiv_{\Module k}\;
    \HModule\,k\,F\,n.
  \]
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  Use $\mathtt{Eq.symm} \blacktriangleright$ on iter-029's $\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare\_toSquare\_X_4}$ to transport the witness $\mathtt{Preorder.isTerminalTop}\,(\mathtt{TopologicalSpace.Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat}) : \IsTerminal\,(\top : \mathtt{Opens}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})$ to an $\IsTerminal\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)$. Apply Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_eq_HModule_linearEquiv} (iter-034) at this terminal corner. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-035 pass) confirms the one-liner typechecks end-to-end and produces kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{definition}[$\AffineCoverMVSquare.X_4$ specialisation, curve form, iter-035]
  \label{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.HModule'_X₄_linearEquiv_curve}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv, def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\of\,k))$ (a $k$-scheme), $S : C.\mathtt{left}.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $n : \N$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for $\Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$. There is a $k$-linear isomorphism
  \[
    \HModulePrime\,k\,(\Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)
    \;\equiv_{\Module k}\;
    \HModule\,k\,(\Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n.
  \]
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  Direct application of Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv} to $F := \Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C$, via the dot-notation method-call form $S.\mathtt{HModule}'\_\mathtt{X}_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}\,k\,\_\,n$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-035 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
